{
  "text": "Age-related macular degeneration is the leading cause of irreversible blindness in the Western world. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] In the United States alone, nearly two million individuals are afflicted with severe, end-stage AMD, and are legally blind. Seven million more have early stage AMD, or agerelated maculopathy, and are at high risk for developing advanced AMD. [CITATION_4] As the population ages, the negative impact of AMD on society will increase. [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] Defining 'macrophages'",
